Etymology[edit]

From prōdūcō +‎ -tō (frequentative suffix)

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /proːˈduk.toː/, [proːˈd̪ʊk.t̪oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /proˈduk.to/, [prɔˈd̪uk.t̪ɔ]

Verb[edit]

prōductō (present infinitive prōductāre, perfect active prōductāvī, supine prōductātum); first conjugation

  1. I throw before, interpose
